main event: Various sightings of starlike objects reported in Lyndhurst, New Jersey, between January and July 1967, concluded as satellites.
interesting points: The original report mentioned a questionable sighting that was not satisfactorily handled., Several starlike objects were observed at specific times and directions., The conclusion of the sightings was that they were satellites., Poor photograph quality rendered photo analysis unnecessary., Echo satellites were noted as being bright and visible to the naked eye.
